ext steps:\n1. Reproduce from a clean worktree starting at `16780b6983941dfac04aa459ccedf9093d0322b3` and confirm whether `:compileTestScala` still fails on the missing `FromInput.SeqFromInput` type.\n2. Compare the successful later run state with the preserved branch to identify what test source or generated files existed when the later `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` runs were produced, and why no patch/artifacts were recorded in metrics.\n3. If the later successful logs are valid, rerun the human-intervention workflow or preserve the passing test sources; otherwise manually update the Scala test to the 1.1.0-RC1 `FromInput` API and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.sangria-graphql:sangria-marshalling-api_3:1.1.0-RC1`."}}
